            <title class="- topic/title " xtrc="title:2;58:20" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/controlled-values-for-attributes.dita">Example: Controlled values that provide additional information about the
                subject</title>
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrc="p:5;60:16" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/controlled-values-for-attributes.dita">The following code fragment illustrates how a subject definition can provide a richer
                level of information about a controlled value:</p>
            <codeblock class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xml:space="preserve" xtrc="codeblock:1;62:24" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/controlled-values-for-attributes.dita">&lt;subjectdef keys="terminology" href="https://www.oasis-open.org/policies-guidelines/keyword-guidelines"&gt;
  &lt;subjectdef keys="rfc2119" href="rfc-2119.dita"&gt;
    &lt;topicmeta&gt;
      &lt;navtitle&gt;RFC-2119 terminology&lt;/navtitle&gt;
